--- !u!114 &170865137
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 170865136}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 50eb2720e91e1f948bebd8f5b62bc4db, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::VisionSequence
  introClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 33a66a461383aba4384533851e890c87, type: 3}
  loopClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 2e1d38da363f23649bca33b3fc648203, type: 3}
  musicSource: {fileID: 321143794}
  speakerName: ???
  speakerPortrait: {fileID: -1129053613409444506, guid: 954e9c5828c05644392c1ab6b3a49f96, type: 3}
  lines:
  - '<align="center">

    Only few know the realities unfolding before us.

    Worlds
    are collapsing into each other, triggering cascading events.'
  - "<align=\"center\">\nKhatun has been stripped from her world.\nIn her final moments,
    she attempted to sacrifice herself to protect the last bastion of humanity.\n "
  - '<align="center">

    But Her Moon would not let her draw any more power.

    Her
    priestesses channeled every remaining ounce of energy in hopes to save their
    world, forcing her sacrifice to tap in to the energy of yours. '
  - "<align=\"center\">\nFor a priestess to gather energy, she must create a negative
    void.\nThe Hollow, as it is taught, starts out small, and fills fast in a healthy
    world. \nBut her world was damaged. "
  - '<align="center">Her Hollow grew too fast, gaining size as it searched for energy.

    Unfortunately,
    the larger the Hollow grows, the more unstable it becomes.

    As the void of
    energy ripped through her world, its instability ruptured through the bindings
    of reality. '
  - "<align=\"center\">Your Moon answered her call. \nIts Energy ripped through the
    sky and shattered the barrier between worlds, and although the Hollow is intended
    to receive energy, its void had become too large for her to control. "
  - '<align="center">

    As your world''s energy rushed to her, her Hollow ripped
    her from her world directly to the energy of yours, and vaulted her to you. '
  - '<align="center">

    This was the trap that Oksana laid out.

    <b>Oksana,
    the True Harbinger. '
  - "<align=\"center\">\nShe is the being who destroyed Khatun's world.\nShe is the
    Bringer of Light.\n "
  - '<align="center">

    Her intent was to empower your moon as Khatun drew from
    it.

    She brought more than Khatun.

    She brought the Plague of Light. '
  - '<align="center">

    Khatun, however, was supposed to be alone.

    She was
    to be overwhelmed by what had occured.

    Khatun was to be swallowed by Oksana''s
    Light Amalgamations.'
  - '<align="center">

    But you were there to stop them.

    A cog in the gears
    of Oksana''s Machine.'
  - '<align="center">

    You must continue to be that cog.

    You must help Khatun
    regain her power.'
  - '<align="center">Oksana interfaces with two sides of a coin.

    The Light and
    The Shadow.

    She is a native to the power of the Light.

    The power of
    Shadow channels itself from The Moon, and her interference has corrupted the
    veins of energy that draw from The Moon. '
  - "<align=\"center\">\n\nHowever, she is ignorant to the Energy beneath her very
    feet.\nYou must empower Khatun with the Energy of the Earth.\n\n "
  - "<align=\"center\">\n\nI empower you, my cog, with \n<b><color=#3A040A>The Binding
    of the Earth</b></color>\n "
  delayBeforeDialogue: 1.5
  nextSceneName: Town
